// GPU kernel correctness. On a machine with a GPU/OpenCL device this runs
// every GPU kernel (tiled matmul, elementwise) against the CPU reference and
// checks they agree to fp32 tolerance. On a CPU-only host it reports SKIP and
// passes -- there is nothing to verify. Either way the line below must appear,
// so the test confirms the GPU self-check path is wired up and callable.
// EXPECT: GPU:
fn app() { gpu_selftest(); return 0.0; }
